'''International Association of Independent Tanker Owners (INTERTANKO)''' is the association of the owner of the independent [[tanker (ship)|tanker]]s in the world. It started in 1970 to speak out for the independent tankers' owners, non-oil companies and non-state controlled tanker owners, for the safe shipping of [[oil]] and [[chemical]]s and to act as a forum for marine policy creation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.londoninternationalshippingweek.com/organizer/intertanko/ |title=London International Shipping Week - INTERTANKO|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref> Membership is open to independent tanker owners and operators of oil and chemical tankers, i.e. non-oil companies and non-state controlled tanker owners, who fulfil the Association's membership criteria. Independent owners operate some 80% of the world's tanker fleet and the vast majority are INTERTANKO members. As of January 2012, the organisation had 235 members, whose combined fleet comprises some 3,380 tankers totalling 285 million dwt. INTERTANKO's associate membership stands at some 320 companies with an interest in shipping of oil and chemicals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.intertanko.com/About-Us/|title= INTERTANKO Website - About Us|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>
INTERTANKO are responsible for the compilation of several marine industry books and publications. [[Witherby Seamanship]] are the official distributors of [[INTERTANKO]] publications.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.intertanko.com/News-Desk/Press-Releases/Year-2013/Witherbys-to-manage-the-sales-and-distribution-of-INTERTANKO-publications/ |title=INTERTANKO and Witherby|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref> INTERTANKO's central offices are in [[Oslo]], [[Norway]] and in [[London]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/FC019382|title=Companies House - INTERTANKO|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>
==External links== * [http://www.intertanko.com/templates/Page.aspx?id=1086 The International Association of Independent Tanker Owners (INTERTANKO) official site].
